From Mark Haun Subject Re bit A D converter In article A Max Corbin writes Once upon a time, long long ago in this news group, someone posted a schematic for a bit A D converter Well I just found a use for the little monster Anyone out there still got this text file It had a flip flop, a resistor and a cap, and a comparator op amp I think I would be extremely thankful to anyone who could mail me the schematic or post it to the news group Hmmm how about a piece of copper wire to V input range, standard TTL output, instantaneous conversion time for the humor impaired Mark A Haun INTERNET Sittner Hall Amateur Radio KJ PC College Place, WA